cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT

This paper deals with the problem of routing data packets in a Vehicular Sensor Network (VSN), which is a type of wireless sensor network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also uses statistical analysis and optimization techniques to develop an optimal routing policy, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also deals with the problem of minimizing delay, which could place it in cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
